{{Quote|The scum of the galaxy pass through Stenness on their way to the Rim.|Unattributed|<ref name="FF11" />}}
The '''Stenness Node''', was a group of three<ref name="TotJ4" /><ref name="FF11" /> mining [[Star system/Legends|systems]] in the [[Inner Rim/Legends|Inner Rim]],<ref name="TEA" /> known collectively as the '''Stenness worlds''',<ref name="TotJ4" /> the '''Stenness systems''',<ref name="TOTJC" /><ref name="SWI26">{{InsiderCite|26|The Horse's Mouth|Straight from the Horse's Mouth: A Guide to the ''Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi'' Universe, Part 1}}</ref> or simply the '''Stenness system'''.<ref name="FF11" /> There were twenty-five [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoid]] [[Species/Legends|races]] native to the Stenness Node, collectively called "[[Nessie]]s."<ref name="TotJ4" /> The [[Space station/Legends|space station]] known as [[The Rig]] was located in an [[asteroid field]] in this region. The Node comprised of seven inhabited mining [[Planet|worlds]],<ref name="AGttSWU2E">''[[A Guide to the Star Wars Universe, Second Edition, Revised and Expanded]]'' {{C|"Stenness" entry}}</ref><ref name="RD">''[[Rebel Dawn]]''</ref> including, [[Ithull]], [[Taboon]],<ref name="TotJ4" /> and [[Kamsul]],<ref name="RD" /> as well as an asteroid field,<ref name="SWR65" /> with [[Ambria]] at the heart of the Node.<ref name="TotJ3" />

==History==
Designated by the [[Republic Survey Team]] as the Stenness Node, there was controversy over the regions correct name, as it was also reported as the Stenness Systems. The naming controversy even reached as far as the [[Senate]].<ref name="TOTJC" />

The [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] crime lord [[Bogga]] was a major power in the Stenness Node in the years before the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Great Sith War]], often dwelling in the [[Stenness Hyperspace Terminal]] when not holding court in his headquarters on the moon of [[Vo Dasha]]. For a hefty fee, the Hutt's enslaved henchmen and modified [[Core Galaxy Systems Dreadnaught]] [[Enforcer One (dreadnaught)|''Enforcer One'']] would protect the Nessies and their mining operations from raids by pirates such as [[Finhead Stonebone]] and his motley crew of cut-throats.

Millennia later, [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Salla Zend]] smuggled [[Spice/Legends|spice]] to the system.<ref name="DEE">[[Dark Empire endnotes|''Dark Empire'' endnotes]]</ref><ref name="RD" /> Crimelord [[BolBol]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] was known to be practically in control of the Node as of [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]].

==Behind the scenes==
The node originally appeared spelled as "Stenness Node" however it is occasionally misspelled as "Stennes Node"<ref name="PotJS">''[[Power of the Jedi Sourcebook]]''</ref> and "Steness Node"<ref name="SWR65" /> in some later sources.

The ''[[Tales of the Jedi Companion]]'' claimed that the [[Japrael system/Legends|Onderon system]] was in the Stenness Node, however, in the actual comic appearances of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]], it is stated to be on "the other side of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]" from the Node. This error was repeated in the [[Star Wars Gamer 1|''Star Wars Gamer'' 1]] article ''[[The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Marvel Series]]'' which erroneously grouped the Ambria, [[Amar system/Legends|Amar]] and [[Japrael system|Onderon]] systems together within the Node.<ref name="TUSGIL">{{GamerCite|1|The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Marvel Series}}</ref> Of the three systems mentioned in the ''[[Star Wars Gamer]]'' article, the Ambria system is the only confirmed by other sources to specifically reside within the Node.<ref name="TotJ4" /><ref name="TOTJC" />

[[HoloNet News Vol. 531 46]] includes reference to the "[[Stenness Data Node]]" but does not elaborate what this relates to.<ref name="HNN46">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|46|regional/1337_5.html|Merson Pirates Attack Sy Myrth Liner}}</ref>

